    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-07-14T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-07-14T05:00:00-05:00" n="28"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d28">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.3 B 1/184: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-07-14T11:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 14, 1924—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>58. On July 12 the Temporary Mixed Commission adjourned. The draft convention
                    which the Commission drew up will be submitted in September to the Assembly of
                    the League of Nations. The draft convention as approved by the Assembly will be
                    submitted later to an international conference for negotiation. An invitation
                    will be given to the interested governments to attend this conference.</p>
                <p>The draft as approved by the Commission seems to be in harmony with the
                    Department’s views as indicated by its instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
